<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="204" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/1720: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-29T15:00:00-04:00">June 29,
                                1943—3 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>823. Reference Moscow’s telegram no. 663, June 15, 10 a.m. (which was
                        repeated to you) quoting Vladivostok’s telegram no. 65, June 11, 11 a.m.</p>
                    <p>The Department would like to have any information you have or may be able to
                        obtain on this subject.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>